full_summary:
### Gravel Application – Grasslands National Park
#### solicitation number: 5P420-23-0129/A

The Parks Canada Agency is seeking bids for the supply and application of Type 105 or 106 and Type 103 traffic gravel to various locations within Grasslands National Park for routine road maintenance.

#### Solicitation Period
The solicitation period for this project begins on September 14, 2023, and closes on October 10, 2023, at 16:00:00. All bids must be received by the specified deadline.

#### Contact Information
For any technical or contractual inquiries, please contact Terry Imm at Terry.Imm@pc.gc.ca or (250) 837-1659.

#### Requirements
Parks Canada requires the supply and application of traffic gravel to various locations within Grasslands National Park. Bidders must be able to provide Type 105 or 106 and Type 103 traffic gravel in accordance with the National Parks Regulations.

#### Tender Description
The Contract period is from date of Contract to November 6, 2023, inclusive. Bidders are advised that only bids submitted by fax and email will be accepted as official. The only acceptable email address for responses to the bid solicitation is soumissionsouest-bidswest@canada.ca. The Crown retains the right to negotiate with suppliers on any procurement.

All enquiries regarding this solicitation must be submitted in writing and should be received no later than seven (7) calendar days prior to the closing date. The size of the email is limited to 15 megabytes, and bidders must ensure that their submission does not exceed this limit. Attachments to the email should not contain links to bid documents. 

Bidders are required to base their bids on documents obtained from the Government Electronic Tendering Service through the Government of Canada tendering service at http://canadabuys.canada.ca/en/tender-opportunities. Addenda, when issued, will be available from the Government of Canada tendering service.

#### Tender Submission
Bids must be submitted in either English or French. Bidders are advised that the Government of Canada's standard payment terms will apply to all successful bidders.
